"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"New Gutenberg Ticket &amp; RSVP Blocks";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-ticket-rsvp-blocks/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 23 Oct 2018 15:23:43 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Articles";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"News & Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Block Editor";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"events gutenberg";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Gutenberg";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1647032";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:587:"<p>Since the beginning of the year (and even a bit before that), our team has been hard at work preparing our plugins for the upcoming block editor release in WordPress 5.0. We’ve already released several event blocks in our Events Gutenberg extension and we’re proud to announce ticket blocks and RSVP blocks are now available!&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-ticket-rsvp-blocks/">New Gutenberg Ticket &#038; RSVP Blocks</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"Jen";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12223:"<p>Since the beginning of the year (and even a bit before that), our team has been hard at work preparing our plugins for the upcoming block editor release in WordPress 5.0. We’ve already released several event blocks in our Events Gutenberg extension and we’re proud to announce <strong>ticket blocks and RSVP blocks are now available!</strong></p>\n<p>Below you’ll find screenshots of the design work for our new blocks. You can take ‘em for a spin on your own site by downloading our <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/extensions/events-gutenberg/">Events Gutenberg extension</a>.</p>\n<p><em>Note: These blocks are only available when also running <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets/">Event Tickets</a> (and optionally <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-event-tickets-plus/">Event Tickets Plus</a>). </em></p>\n<blockquote><p>Not familiar with the block editor yet? Snag our free <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-block-editor-free-ebook/">Guide to Gutenberg ebook</a>!</p></blockquote>\n<h2>Event RSVP Blocks</h2>\n<p>Our new Gutenberg RSVP block makes it easy for admins to add RSVP functionality when creating or editing an event, and even easier for attendees to snag a spot at your event when viewing it on your site.</p>\n<h4>Backend Admin Options for the RSVP Block</h4>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1647034" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin.jpg" alt="Gutenberg RSVP Block for Event Tickets and Event Tickets Plus" width="675" height="666" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin.jpg 675w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-86x85.jpg 86w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-300x296.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-665x656.jpg 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-430x424.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-645x636.jpg 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-460x454.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-100x100.jpg 100w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-600x592.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-admin-500x493.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 675px) 100vw, 675px" /></p>\n<h4>Frontend View of the RSVP Block</h4>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1647035" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE.jpg" alt="Gutenberg RSVP Block view on the frontend" width="616" height="178" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE.jpg 616w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-140x40.jpg 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-300x87.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-430x124.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-460x133.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-600x173.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/RSVP-block-FE-500x144.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 616px) 100vw, 616px" /></p>\n<h2>Event Ticket Blocks</h2>\n<p>Creating tickets is a snap with our new event ticket block. The main ticket options are available as soon as you open the block, with advanced settings only a quick click away. During setup, you can set ticket descriptions and capacity, and once sales have started, you’ll also see how many tickets have been sold.</p>\n<p>Visual parity between the edit screen and what your attendees see on the frontend makes it easy to create an optimized layout that increases sales conversions—no CSS or custom code required!</p>\n<h4>Backend Admin Options for the Ticket Block</h4>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1647036" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation.jpg" alt="Gutenberg Ticket Block admin backend options" width="676" height="1106" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation.jpg 676w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-52x85.jpg 52w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-183x300.jpg 183w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-626x1024.jpg 626w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-430x704.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-645x1055.jpg 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-460x753.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-300x491.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-489x800.jpg 489w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-admin-creation-500x818.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px" /></p>\n<h4>Frontend View of the Ticket Block</h4>\n<p>Remember that visual parity we just mentioned? Here’s how it looks on the frontend when attendees view your registration page: same ticket order, same remaining quantity available, and (of course) straightforward options to select the number of tickets they want to purchase.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1647037" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE.jpg" alt="Gutenberg Ticket Block Frontend Attendee View" width="616" height="548" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE.jpg 616w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-96x85.jpg 96w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-300x267.jpg 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-430x383.jpg 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-460x409.jpg 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-600x534.jpg 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/10/tickets-FE-500x445.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 616px) 100vw, 616px" /></p>\n<h2>More to Come!</h2>\n<p>This release is but the first of several as we steadily build block editor support across our plugin suite. Attendee Registration functionality, front-end attendee lists, and ticket/RSVP support for non-event post types are still under development to be included in future releases.</p>\n<p>As we advance our Gutenberg work to provide compatibility for all of our plugins, we’ll continue to <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/extensions/events-gutenberg/">share new blocks</a> as they are released.</p>\n<p><em>Sign up here to get the <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-block-editor-news/">latest announcements</a> on our Gutenberg progress and other news from The Events Calendar delivered straight to your inbox.</em></p>\n\n                <div class=''gf_browser_unknown gform_wrapper'' id=''gform_wrapper_28'' ><form method=''post'' enctype=''multipart/form-data''  id=''gform_28''  action=''/feed/''>\n                        <div class=''gform_body''><ul id=''gform_fields_28'' class=